Description: Body sherd of Chian pottery open vessel, perhaps a cup; white slip; interior glazed streaky black with single added red band above faded added white band; exterior: slip partly worn; band of short rays between black c bands with added red lines. Orientation of sherd uncertain.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GD.1922) (phase 2)
